TY  - JOUR
TI  - Optimal Savings Policy When Labor Grows Endogenously
AU  - Sato, Ryuzo
AU  - Davis, Eric G.
AB  - [This paper is an attempt to study optimal savings policy in a world where the growth rate of labor responds to economic factors. This modification makes the form of society's social welfare function important--its elasticity affects "real" economic variables. In addition, a rule for direct population control is investigated.]
C1  - Full publication date: Nov., 1971
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1909665
